Luke Hurley is an independent New Zealand guitarist and singer-songwriter, who works mostly outside the confines of the music industry. He was born in Kenya on the 31st of August,1957 and moved with his family to Gore in Southland, New Zealand when aged 12. He achieved a degree of early success on student radio with the song &quot;Mona Lisa&quot; in the early 1980s at University of Otago in Dunedin. &lt;a href=&quot;
